"title": "8330: receptiveness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8330",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An openness to people and ideas which needs to be tempered by discernment. It is an attitude which God desires and which he shows to all who call to him.</p>\n<h2>Receptiveness as a human quality</h2>\n<h3>It is characterised by an open attitude</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:16-Matt13:17\">MAT 13:16–13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:15\">PRO 18:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:12\">PRO 20:12</a></p>\n<h3>It is an aspect of love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:26-John19:27\">JHN 19:26–19:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:3-Ruth4:5\">RUT 4:3–4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:13\">RUT 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:5\">MAT 18:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:37\">MRK 9:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:48\">LUK 9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:35\">MAT 25:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:44-Acts2:45\">ACT 2:44–2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:32\">ACT 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:6-1Cor13:7\">1CO 13:6–13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:14\">GAL 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Thoughtful receptiveness requires discernment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:1\">1JN 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:14\">1CO 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:10\">PHP 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:21\">1TH 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:14\">HEB 5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Thoughtless receptiveness is dangerous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3-2Cor11:4\">2CO 11:3–11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:16\">DEU 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:4\">1KI 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:21\">PRO 7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:8\">COL 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:9\">HEB 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:10\">2JN 1:10</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual receptiveness is fruitful</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:5\">JHN 15:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:3\">PSA 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:5-Prov3:6\">PRO 3:5–3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:20-Prov6:22\">PRO 6:20–6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:7-Jer17:8\">JER 17:7–17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:29\">JHN 20:29</a></p>\n<h2>God is receptive to human beings</h2>\n<h3>To their needs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:36\">MAT 9:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:26\">2KI 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:13-Ps103:14\">PSA 103:13–103:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:9\">ISA 63:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:8\">MAT 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:32\">MAT 15:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:2-Mark8:3\">MRK 8:2–8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:13\">LUK 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:7\">1PE 5:7</a></p>\n<h3>To their cries</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:9\">PSA 38:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:7\">EXO 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:3\">1KI 9:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:12\">2CH 7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:8-Ps6:9\">PSA 6:8–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:1\">PSA 40:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:24\">ISA 65:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>To their repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:1-Hos14:4\">HOS 14:1–14:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13\">2SA 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:27-Ezek18:28\">EZK 18:27–18:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:13\">JOL 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:10\">JON 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:2\">JON 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:7\">LUK 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:10\">LUK 15:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:13–18:14</a></p>\n<h3>God's receptiveness may be withdrawn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:13\">ZEC 7:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:18\">PSA 66:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:13\">PRO 21:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:11\">JER 11:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:23\">MAT 7:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:7\">JAS 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>People should be receptive to God</h2>\n<h3>Spiritual receptiveness begins by receiving Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:40\">MAT 10:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41\">ACT 2:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:14\">ACT 16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:6\">COL 2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual receptiveness requires openness to God's Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:12-1Cor2:16\">1CO 2:12–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5\">ROM 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:16\">ROM 8:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:40\">1CO 7:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16\">GAL 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:25\">GAL 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Receptiveness involves seeking and listening</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:4-Isa50:5\">ISA 50:4–50:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:29\">DEU 4:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:11\">PSA 119:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:34\">PRO 8:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:8\">MAT 7:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:10\">LUK 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:39\">LUK 10:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:18\">EPH 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:19\">JAS 1:19</a></p>\n<h3>Receptiveness involves accepting and learning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:15\">MRK 10:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:17\">LUK 18:17</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:2\">PSA 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:1\">LUK 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:27\">JHN 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:45\">JHN 6:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:30-Acts8:31\">ACT 8:30–8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:11\">ACT 17:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:13\">1TH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">1JN 2:27</a></p>\n<h3>Receptiveness requires obedience and action</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:23\">JHN 14:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:22\">1SA 15:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:6-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:6–58:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:21\">MAT 7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:17\">JHN 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:17\">JHN 7:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:25\">JAS 1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:14\">JAS 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10\">1PE 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>Refusing to be receptive to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:11-Zech7:12\">ZEC 7:11–7:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:19\">2CH 24:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:33\">JER 32:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:14\">MAT 10:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:11\">MRK 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:5\">LUK 9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:11\">JHN 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:51-Acts7:53\">ACT 7:51–7:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:7-Jas1:8\">JAS 1:7–1:8</a></p>",
